Class JkDependencyResolver<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • dev.jeka.core.api.depmanagement.resolution.JkDependencyResolver<T>

    Class to resolve dependencies to files or dependency tree. Resolution is made upon binary repositories.

      • setModuleHolder

        public JkDependencyResolver<T> setModuleHolder(JkVersionedModule versionedModule)
        The underlying dependency manager can cache the resolution on file system for faster result. To make this caching possible, you must set the module+version for which the resolution is made. This is only relevant for of dependencies and have no effect for of dependencies.

      • resolve

        public JkResolveResult resolve(JkQualifiedDependencies qualifiedDependencies)
        Resolves the specified dependencies (dependencies declared as module) for the specified scopes.
        Parameters:
        qualifiedDependencies - the dependencies to resolve.
        Returns:
        a result consisting in a dependency tree for modules and a set of files for non-module.
